value: Breeds from central Alberta, southeastern Saskatchewan, Manitoba, southern Quebec and Newfoundland, south to the Gulf Coast and Florida and west to east-central Montana and eastern Texas. Winter range unknown, presumably in Amazonian South America, recorded on migra- tion in Mexico, Central America and Hispaniola.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Open situations and woodland, especially around human habitation; now nests and roosts primarily in chimneys, originally on cliffs or in hollow trees.

subcat_descr: Bill length (sex unknown) - Nares to tip
